{
  "texts": [
    "We can also use LLMs to evaluate and refine user questions instantly as they perform well in prompting [60].",
    "Turning to the Temporal Dynamics of LLM-Powered Tutoring ToolsThe temporality aspect of using CodeTutor in computer science education presents a nuanced perspective on their integration and effectiveness over time.",
    "Our analysis reveals a complex relationship between the duration of CodeTutor use and students' attitudes towards it.",
    "Specifically, our results show that although students initially find CodeTutor a reliable tool for understanding their queries, their confidence in its accuracy diminishes with prolonged use.",
    "Additionally, our model uncovers a weakly significant decrease in students' preference for CodeTutor as a TA replacement over time."
  ]
}